## Code Block Reference

```ts
import LazyPlot from '$lib/components/LazyPlot.svelte';
import * as plotConfigs from '$lib/plotConfigs';

// Use factory functions that create data/layout on-demand
<LazyPlot
	dataFactory={plotConfigs.createSineCosineData}
	layoutFactory={plotConfigs.createSineCosineLayout}
	style="width: 100%; height: 500px;"
/>;
```

The snippet above shows how plots are lazy-loaded in this postâ€”they only load when scrolled into view, keeping the page fast. The LazyPlot component uses Intersection Observer to defer Plotly import and data computation until needed, preventing the page freeze that would occur if all plots loaded upfront. All within SvelTeX so you can mix prose, LaTeX, and components effortlessly.

